stopLimitDescription: A Stop Limit order to ##side## ##volume## Units of ##symbol## contains both a stop price and a limit price. When market price ##increasesFalls## to ##stopPrice## or surpasses it, the stop price is triggered and the order will become a limit order to ##side## ##volume## ##symbol## at ##limitPrice## or ##lowHigh##
limitDescription: A Limit order to ##side## ##volume## Units of ##symbol## can only be executed at ##limitPrice## or ##lowHigh##
marketToLimitDescription: A Market to Limit order to ##side## ##volume## Units of ##symbol## is submitted as a market order to execute at the best ##bidOffer## price available in the market. If the order is only partially filled, the remaining quantity of the order is cancelled and re-submitted as a limit order with the limit price equal to the price at which the filled portion of the order is executed.
marketDescription: A Market order to ##side## ##volume## Units of ##symbol## is submitted as a market order to execute at the best ##bidOffer## price available in the market. If the order is only partially filled, the remaining quantity of the order is cancelled and re-submitted as a limit order with the limit price equal to the price at which the filled portion of the order is executed.
trailingStopLimitBuyDescription: A Trailing Stop Limit order to ##side## ##volume## Units of ##symbol## contains trailing stop price, ##trailLable## ##trailValue##, and limit price. The initial trailing stop price is ##trailingStopPrice## If the market price decreases, the trailing stop price will move lower, and be equal to market price plus ##trailLable##. However, if the market price increases, the trailing stop price will remain the same. Once the stop price is triggered, the order will become a limit order to ##side## ##volume## ##symbol## at ##limitPrice##, or lower
trailingStopLimitSellDescription: A Trailing Stop Limit order to ##side## ##volume## Units of ##symbol## contains trailing stop price, ##trailLable## ##trailValue##, and limit price. The initial trailing stop price is ##trailingStopPrice## If the market price increases, the trailing stop price will move higher, and be equal to market price minus ##trailLable##. However, if the market price decreases, the trailing stop price will remain the same. Once the stop price is triggered, the order will become a limit order to ##side## ##volume## ##symbol## at ##limitPrice##, or higher
